news.title: Gurugram: Soon, Vipul World to get new power connections
news.para: DHBVN had also asked the developer of the project to submit the bank guarantee and hand over 500 square yards of land for constructing a 33kV substation.

news.title: Sanjaynagar scheme among biggest in India under PMAY: Vadodara Mayor
news.para: The Sanjaynagar housing scheme for the urban poor under the Pradhan Mantri Aavas Yojana (PMAY) is now being touted to be amongst the biggest of its kind in the country. Work on the scheme formally began after a long delay on Monday.

news.title: Nashik civic body makes names of 600 big property tax defaulters public
news.para: The civic body has uploaded the list of the defaulters on its official website and requested them to clear their dues at the earliest. These 600 defaulters owe over Rs 40 crore to the civic body — ranging from Rs 1 lakh to over Rs 20 lakh each.

news.title: Dehradun civic body sends notices to 10,000 property tax defaulters
news.para: The scrutiny is still on and as more wards are covered, more defaulters may be identified soon, DMC officials said, adding that if they fail to make payment, they will be penalised.

news.title: Haryana: Call for Aadhaar card checks during registry of properties
news.para: The officials also suggested introducing an online system for people to get duplicate copies of revenue documents of their property. Currently, a person needs to visit the revenue office to get a copy of the document.

news.title: Allahabad HC seeks Ghaziabad development body's report on housing scam
news.para: The division bench of Chief Justice Rajesh Bindal and Justice Vikram D Chauhan also directed that cases pending in the district courts in connection with the scam be clubbed with the main petition.

news.title: Greater Noida: 25 builder projects extracting groundwater illegally
news.para: The committee - comprising the Noida district magistrate and officials from the state and central pollution control boards — was formed in July following allegations that 63 projects of some 40 builders were involved in extracting groundwater illegally.

news.title: Delhi HC asks police to reply to Sushil Ansal's plea in evidence tampering case
news.para: Justice Purushaindra Kumar Kaurav issued notice to the Delhi Police on the 83-year-old Ansal's petition and listed the matter for further hearing on December 13.

news.title: Officials must atone for Amrapali mess: Supreme Court
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice U U Lalit and Bela M Trivedi reminded them that they were also party to creating this problem and asked them to make an exception for Amrapali projects to ensure that construction work is completed.

news.title: Eight builders attend pre-bid meet for Dharavi redevelopment plan
news.para: ​​A special purpose vehicle will be formed by the lead bidder along with the Slum Rehabilitation Authority and the Dharavi Redevelopment Authority to execute the project.

news.title: Dues deadlock: As registry wait for Noida flats gets longer, all eyes on SC for relief
news.para: Builders argue they will not pay the dues till the Supreme Court, which is hearing the case, comes up with a verdict. Homebuyers are worried because without a registry, they do not have legal rights over their flats and can't sell the properties.

news.title: Rustomjee inks pact to develop 2-million-sq-ft affordable housing project in Kalyan
news.para: The company, which is currently in the process of raising funds through its initial public offer (IPO), is planning to invest over Rs 500 crore to develop the project that will be completed in the next five years.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Draft coastal zone management plan out; feedback sought within a month
news.para: The map had indicated 11 categories of locations as 'no development zones'. They have been classified as ecosystems, geomorphological sites, habitats and heritage sites.

news.title: Archives department to digitise land papers to prevent fraud: Goa minister
news.para: Minister for archives Subhash Phal Dessai said that people have fraudulently used land documents from the archives department and claimed ownership on land.

news.title: Smartworks leases 1.7 lakh sq ft in Jaipur and Indore
news.para: Smartworks plans to add another three million sq ft this fiscal year, bringing its total portfolio to 10 million sq ft.
